# Interactive View Prose Review

## Summary
The draft was well-structured and accurate. One section required improvement to provide concrete enum values instead of vague descriptions.

## Changes Made

### 1. Key Input Behavior Section — Expanded Policy Description
**Original prose:**
> Control how key events trigger clicks using `KeyClickPolicy`. The policy determines whether key presses trigger the click on key down, key up, or other behaviors.

**Revised prose:**
> Control how key events trigger clicks using `KeyClickPolicy`. The available policies are:
> - `KeyClickPolicy::ON_RELEASE` — Trigger click when the key is released.
> - `KeyClickPolicy::ON_PRESS` — Trigger click immediately when the key is pressed.
> - `KeyClickPolicy::DISABLED` — Disable click events from key inputs.
> This policy applies to D-Pad, remote, or keyboard interactions.

**Source evidence:** `repos/dali-ui/dali-ui-foundation/public-api/key-click-policy.h` defines the `KeyClickPolicy` enum with `ON_RELEASE`, `ON_PRESS`, and `DISABLED` values. The header comment states "This policy is specifically for D-Pad, Remote, or Keyboard interactions."

**Rationale:** The original description was vague ("other behaviors"). Replaced with concrete enum values from the public header to improve accuracy and developer utility.

